HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1429
By Parkinson
A RESOLUTION to recognize Vanessa M. Horner on the occasion
of her retirement from the General Assembly.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this body should honor those valuable
legislative employees who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm
throughout their years of meritorious service to the General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, Vanessa M. Horner is one such estimable person, who has served with
distinction as an exemplary employee of the General Assembly and will be taking her much-
deserved retirement in May 2026; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Horner began her illustrious career with the State of Tennessee in
January 1987, when she began employment with the Tennessee Department of
Correction/Youth Development, a position she held for eight years; and
WHEREAS, Vanessa Horner joined the General Assembly in January 1995 in the office
of Representative Ulysses Jones, Jr., and she began working for Representative Antonio
Parkinson in January 2011; and
WHEREAS, she is grateful for the love and support she shares with her children and
their spouses, Lakesa and Danarius Fowler and George and Melody Strain, Jr.; her
grandchildren, Elijah Burdette, Keaton Cooper, Deyhan Lyons, Kennedy Fowler, and Kobe
Fowler; her great-grandson, Kairo Cooper; her mother, Helen Pardue; and her siblings, Varita
Cooper, Lonnie Cooper, Rasheedah Pardue, and Shaherah Pardue; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Horner exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community
that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
HJR1429
017963
- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career, Vanessa Horner has demonstrated the
utmost professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of
her colleagues and the leadership and members of the General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we extend to Vanessa M. Horner our heartfelt wishes for a happy and
fulfilling retirement and every continued success in her future endeavors, and we thank her for
her dedicated and efficient service to the General Assembly.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
